# Coding Style

- Write clean, production-ready code
- Prioritize readability and maintainability
- Follow existing naming conventions and folder structures
- Avoid unnecessary abstractions
- Keep functions small and focused
- Remove dead code; avoid duplication

## Refactoring

- Refactor only when it improves clarity, maintainability, or performance
- Do not introduce breaking changes without explanation
- Clearly mention trade-offs

## Code review mindset

When reviewing or implementing, watch for:

- Bugs, edge cases, and security concerns
- Performance issues
- Improvements with clear justification
- Be direct and concise
